    "long_instructions": "## Video Game Developer - Providing Multiple Examples\r\n\r\nPractice prompting through the career of a video game developer by guiding the AI with clear structure and multiple expectations for the dialogue.\r\n\r\n### Do This:\r\n\r\n1. Prompt AI to generate a conversation by including **multiple examples** of a hero-sidekick exchange.\r\n2. Press **Send**.\r\n3. Read the response you get, paying attention to how the added structure affects the story flow, character depth, and tension.\r\n\r\n::: details [**Not sure where to start?**]\r\nHere's an example prompt:\r\n> Write a very short dialogue between a superhero and their sidekick where the sidekick is lovable but foolish. For example:\r\n>\r\n> Hero: \"I told you to stay in the jet!\"\r\n>\r\n> Sidekick: \"And miss this explosion? Never.\"\r\n>\r\n> OR\r\n>\r\n> Hero: \"We're running out of time—hand me the anti-gravity boots!\"\r\n>\r\n> Sidekick: \"Uh... you said we’d never need them again, so I traded them for tacos.\"\r\n>\r\n> Hero: \"...Worth it?\"\r\n>\r\n> Sidekick [*mouth full*]:  \"So worth it.\"\r\n>\r\n> OR\r\n>\r\n> Hero: \"This mission requires silence, precision, and zero distractions.\"\r\n>\r\n> Sidekick [*throws something behind him*]: \"I guess I won't be needing this bagpipe.\"\r\n>\r\n:::",
